msg: Add a "null" language which produces no triples or quads.

author: desruisseaux
msg: Acknowledge the source of the <T extends Number & Comparable<? super T>> signature.
Note that there is no other way to express the condition "type T extends both Number and Comparable".
So legally, I think that we are okay since anyone wanting to parameterize NumberRange can only obtain
that exact signature; there is no flexibility here (except for the 'T' variable name).  Even the type
order is enforced by the Java language.
